HEADWORD: Setback
<hw>Set"back`</hw> <pr>(s⟦ecr⟧t"b⟦acr⟧k`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>Offset, <pos>n.</pos>, 4.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A backset; a countercurrent; an eddy.</def>
<mark>[U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A reversal of progress in an endeavor; a reverse; a
backset; a check; a repulse; a relapse.</def> <mark>[Colloq.
U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

